<br>
One of the rules I gave before we made our trip to Chardok was about epic drops. &nbsp;<b>I was leaving the looting rights to each particular drop up to the members of the class that needed it.</b> &nbsp;Whim, Lecudian, and I all opted to do a full random (I asked Bridgecrusher to do the roll for me - congratulations to Lecudian on the Prince's head!). &nbsp;The clerics were debating for a few minutes about how to handle the Overking's scroll drop. &nbsp;Bekki sent me a tell that they were considering giving Sinangel the first drop by default if she was present (she had an emergency guild CR to attend and said she would return immediately). &nbsp;If Sinangel wasn't present, or if a 2nd scroll dropped during the raid, it was to be randomed between Bekki and Darikan (who was making the trip to us). &nbsp;Bekki was apparently double and triple checking with the other clerics to make sure they were satisfied with the arrangement, since I got a couple of clerics (sorry, can't remember which) telling me, "We said it was fine. &nbsp;No need to keep asking!"<br>
<br>
When the Overking died, I mentioned that the clerics had already agreed to give the scroll to Sinangel. &nbsp;Darikan was the only one who spoke up against this, but the scroll had already been looted. &nbsp;I was under the impression that all the clerics had agreed to this, and so were others (including non-clerics), as I received several tells from people assuring me that it wasn't my fault if a huge argument came of it.<br>
<br>
Around this time, I was starting to nod off a little. &nbsp;I told BC if the raid was going to continue much longer, that I would pass on the drops I was still holding for someone else to random off. &nbsp;He asked me to stick around for another 30 minutes, so I agreed. &nbsp;About 10-15 minutes later, the Queen was trained to us and we were wiped out. &nbsp;I'm bound up in the Plane of Mischief, so they couldn't summon my corpse with everyone else's right away. &nbsp;I fell asleep while waiting around (there weren't any porters around to get me out, and I didn't know the location to the exit), and didn't actually get back my corpse until around 5am (thanks to Celoria, Fyreflight, and Brodek!).<br>
<br>
Because of the situation with my bindpoint and no easy way to my corpse, I didn't know if anything more was being said about the cleric drop. &nbsp;If Darikan hadn't agreed to that setup, then I feel bad about it... &nbsp;I was <i>sure</i> all the clerics had given the OK prior to breaking in.<br>
<br>
