A good fact for everyone to remember when going on a raid is that not everyone is honest, and not everyone is fair.  Why?  Some folks are a piece of shit IRL and use the game as a way to be greedy selfish lil ratbastards and don't give a damn about everyone around them.  They like to sit in their little room in their mommy and daddy's houses and play this game they don't pay for and think that the world belongs to them.  <br>
<br>
Darikan didn't do anything wrong in this one from what I both saw IG and here.  He got mad and upset, well its true he did, and rightfully so.  I've seen half the folks that posted here do that when they felt screwed.  But it does seem Darikan DID talk to the folks beforehand, and that things DID change. <br>
<br>
NOWHERE was it mentioned to the raid party before it started that Gywenth promised the first item to anyone.  If it was Darikan and the folks he brought wouldnt have gone.  So it does sound like some backstabbing bullshit was going on.  And I'm not saying it was any or all of Sinangel's doing because I don't know.  But I  DO know that for Bekki to get on here and scream at Darikan and insult him sure does point a finger at a probably guilty conspirator.    <br>
<br>
&lt;/tongue in cheek&gt;  Why of course Darikan, you pathetic little fuck, how DARE you point out on this board that things weren't right/fair/true!   Your being mad is just WHINING that you got fucked, and you should shut up and take it and not slander or smear the name of anyone who deserves it, like I'm going to try to do to you.   I don't have to argue your points, I can bury them in namecalling bullshit that I still use in homeroom in junior highschool where I can pretend people still like me.   &lt;/tongue in cheek OFF&gt;<br>
<br>
Yes, it does sound familiar, don't it?   I hope that alot of folks that like to fantasize that they are somoene big and special IRL can one day actually argue facts rather than just call names and deride folks for trying to work things out.  In the meantime, sit in your little trailer in your pile of filth, and play EQ, all the while remaining nothing more than an isecure selfish little nobody.  I'm sure that someday you might become a likable person on the other side of the keyboard.  Just not today or anytime soon.<br>
<br>
<br>
Scratcher<br>
